{%- comment -%}
  Backordered items panel. STUBBED for V1 prototype.

  DATA SOURCE: Stok.ly. Each row in production will come from one
  of these (decision pending, see Stokly_Developer_Questions_v1.md):

    Option A — Per-customer backorder list pushed to a customer
               metafield `stokly.backorders` as a JSON array of
               { sku, title, qty_ordered, qty_shipped, qty_backordered,
                 eta_date, po_number, order_name, line_url }.

    Option B — Live lookup via Theme App Extension calling Stok.ly's
               /customers/{id}/backorders endpoint at render time.

    Recommended: A for V1 (no app dependency, scales fine for MISC's
    customer count), B once volume justifies live-fetched data.

  Until then we render demo rows so the layout is reviewable.
{%- endcomment -%}

<header class="misc-panel__header">
  <h2 class="misc-panel__title">Backordered items</h2>
  <span class="misc-panel__count misc-panel__count--stub">Demo data · Stok.ly TODO</span>
</header>

<p class="misc-panel__intro">
  Items on your past orders that we couldn't ship in full. ETAs come
  from Stok.ly purchase orders and update as suppliers confirm.
</p>

